1.text:
Blessed is the man who doesn’t walk in the counsel of the wicked,
nor stand on the path of sinners,
nor sit in the seat of scoffers;

7.text:
Oh let the wickedness of the wicked come to an end,
but establish the righteous;
their minds and hearts are searched by the righteous God.

9.text:
Have mercy on me, the LORD.
See my affliction by those who hate me,
and lift me up from the gates of death;

12.text:
“Because of the oppression of the weak and because of the groaning of the needy,
I will now arise,” says the LORD;
“I will set him in safety from those who malign him.”

15.text:
He who doesn’t slander with his tongue,
nor does evil to his friend,
nor casts slurs against his fellow man;

In whose eyes a vile man is despised,
but who honors those who fear the LORD;
he who keeps an oath even when it hurts, and doesn’t change;

17.text:
Arise, the LORD, confront him.
Cast him down.
Deliver my soul from the wicked by your sword;

18.text:
The LORD is my rock, my fortress, and my deliverer;
my God, my rock, in whom I take refuge;
my shield, and the horn of my salvation, my high tower.

19.text:
His going out is from the end of the heavens,
his circuit to its ends;
There is nothing hidden from its heat.

22.text:
For he has not despised nor abhorred the affliction of the afflicted,
Neither has he hidden his face from him;
but when he cried to him, he heard.

24.text:
He who has clean hands and a pure heart;
who has not lifted up his soul to falsehood,
and has not sworn deceitfully.

Lift up your heads, you gates;
yes, lift them up, you everlasting doors,
and the King of glory will come in.

27.text:
Now my head will be lifted up above my enemies around me;
I will offer sacrifices of joy in his tent.
I will sing, yes, I will sing praises to the LORD.

Don’t deliver me over to the desire of my adversaries,
for false witnesses have risen up against me,
such as breathe out cruelty.

31.text:
For I have heard the slander of many, terror on every side,
while they conspire together against me,
they plot to take away my life.

35.text:
All my bones shall say, “the LORD, who is like you,
who delivers the poor from him who is too strong for him;
yes, the poor and the needy from him who robs him?”

49.text:
For he sees that wise men die;
likewise the fool and the senseless perish,
and leave their wealth to others.

50.text:
“Hear, my people, and I will speak;
Israel, and I will testify against you.
I am God, your God.

59.text:
For the sin of their mouth, and the words of their lips,
let them be caught in their pride,
for the curses and lies which they utter.

62.text:
God has spoken once;
twice I have heard this,
that power belongs to God.

68.text:
while you sleep among the camp fires,
the wings of a dove sheathed with silver,
her feathers with shining gold.

69.text:
Reproach has broken my heart, and I am full of heaviness.
I looked for some to take pity, but there was none;
for comforters, but I found none.

71.text:
Your righteousness also, God, reaches to the heavens;
you have done great things.
God, who is like you?

My tongue will also talk about your righteousness all day long,
for they are disappointed, and they are confounded,
who want to harm me.

74.text:
Remember your congregation, which you purchased of old,
which you have redeemed to be the tribe of your inheritance;
Mount Zion, in which you have lived.

77.text:
I remember my song in the night.
I consider in my own heart;
my spirit diligently inquires:

Your way was through the sea;
your paths through the great waters.
Your footsteps were not known.

78.text:
from following the ewes that have their young,
he brought him to be the shepherd of Jacob, his people,
and Israel, his inheritance.

85.text:
I will hear what God, the LORD, will speak,
for he will speak peace to his people, his saints;
but let them not turn again to folly.

90.text:
Let the favor of the Lord our God be on us;
establish the work of our hands for us;
yes, establish the work of our hands.

91.text:
A thousand may fall at your side,
and ten thousand at your right hand;
but it will not come near you.

99.text:
Moses and Aaron were among his priests,
Samuel among those who call on his name;
they called on the LORD, and he answered them.

102.text:
You will arise and have mercy on Zion;
for it is time to have pity on her.
Yes, the set time has come.

107.text:
And gathered out of the lands,
from the east and from the west,
from the north and from the south.

131.text:
The LORD, my heart isn’t haughty, nor my eyes lofty;
nor do I concern myself with great matters,
or things too wonderful for me.

133.text:
It is like the precious oil on the head,
that ran down on the beard,
even Aaron’s beard;
that came down on the edge of his robes;

135.text:
who causes the clouds to rise from the ends of the earth;
who makes lightnings with the rain;
who brings the wind out of his treasuries;

138.text:
I will bow down toward your holy temple,
and give thanks to your Name for your loving kindness and for your truth;
for you have exalted your Name and your Word above all.

The LORD will fulfill that which concerns me;
your loving kindness, the LORD, endures forever.
Don’t forsake the works of your own hands.

141.text:
Let the righteous strike me, it is kindness;
let him reprove me, it is like oil on the head;
don’t let my head refuse it;
Yet my prayer is always against evil deeds.

144.text:
Stretch out your hand from above,
rescue me, and deliver me out of great waters,
out of the hands of foreigners;

146.text:
who made heaven and earth,
the sea, and all that is in them;
who keeps truth forever;

who executes justice for the oppressed;
who gives food to the hungry.
The LORD frees the prisoners.

The LORD will reign forever;
your God, O Zion, to all generations.
Praise the LORD!

147.text:
Praise the LORD,
for it is good to sing praises to our God;
for it is pleasant and fitting to praise him.

148.text:
let them praise the LORD’s name,
for his name alone is exalted.
His glory is above the earth and the heavens.
